A major locus controls local adaptation and adaptive life history variation in a perennial plant
European aspen (Populus tremula).
single genomic region containing the PtFT2 gene mediates local adaptation in the timing of bud set and explains 65% of the observed genetic variation in bud set.
https://genomebiology.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13059-018-1444-y#Declarations
